rComments:
Took this over the summer.
Course: very easy until u get to the final exam. Studying off slides is enough but reading the textbook could clear things up.
Prof: not good at explaining things, only has 1.5h of office hours so may be hard to reach, don't bother emailing unless it's something personal (will tell u to put it on the discussion forum)

He was pretty great for this summer. Apart from his final exam (which was tough), his quizzes (almost free marks), assignments and mid-term exams were fair. His lectures were pretty useful and TA for this class was great as well. Highly recommed.

Apart from the long PowerPoint slides, Davood explains the material very well. He answers all the questions which students are in doubt. Quizzes, assignments and mid-term were fair. Recommend him for ADM 3301.
Davood has many assignments but he is super helpful explaining the assignments and teaching the course

Don't take this mug's class unless you are not afraid of heavy workload and lectures with tons of tosh stuff. This prof didn't even complete the class in the Winter term, so our class was taught by another prof who proved himself to be more incompetent and dodgy. His ppt was about 100 pages long and he didn't provide answers for many practice Qs.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: RUN! If you do not have a previous experiences dealing with statistics do not take his class. The recorded lectures are long, boring and confusing, and he doesn't give any summary after teaching a bunch of complicated formulas. Even he's nice and willing to help, still the worst lectures I've had so far.

He is an amazing teacher, and if you attend his lectures, he'll give you a clear understanding of the material. I had statistics second year with him, and the recorded lectures were amazing. Even though half of the assignments are harder than usual, I would definitely take his class again.
I would not take again, I found the lectures were quite disorganized and felt discouraged to ask questions in class.

Davood is the best stats teacher you can have! Very straight forward and his instructions are clear. I highly recommend taking him for stats and operation management. Provides complete powerpoints, great examples and useful assignments and quizzes.
Youll learn all about probability trees and bar charts
Lets just say theres a reason people regularly walk out half way through class, and why David Wrights class has people on the waiting list a month after it starts.
Buddy doesnt know how to explain things. Very disorganized. Read the textbook if you actually want to learn something.
Just read the textbook

Absolutely incredible professor. His lectures were utterly breathtaking. It would never occur to me to sleep or do anything else other than listen to his eloquent and highly comprehensible lectures. Unreal

Telfers worst prof. His excel midterm was extremely difficult. Class avg was 30% when I took it in summer. His exam was extremely difficult. Many students fail his class including myself. Take ops with Rim Jaber she is amazing. Got an A with her. Her lecture notes are more clear. Would not recommend taking ops with davood

Amazing professor. Has clear and easy to follow lectures despite the difficulty of the subject. He takes the time to answer questions clearly so you understand. He cares about his students a lot! Take this professor if you can!

A very caring and friendly professor. He is one of the best professors I've ever seen. If you get the choice, CHOOSE him. He is very helpful and answers your questions diligently. He provides you with all the info you need for the midterm and final. Go to office hours and ask questions, you won't regret it. Overall, he is an AMAZING prof!

I feel like people don't get to know him that well. he is actually an amazing prof. I used to skip classes and say I didn't understand, but if you actually listen to him teach, he's the best! take my word for it
Confusing

Davood is one of the most accurate and caring professors I ever had. He pays attention to the learning of his students and it is important for him that his students leave the class with a new piece in their mind. He expects quality study/participation & I believe it served us very well. He had a wonderful rapport with respect and humor!

He was by far the best professor and friend I have ever had during my years in Telfer. I never missed his class plus he is a very sweet person. Fair and helpful. Helped out with my assignments I wish he was my professor for all my past classes at Telfer. I graduated 2015 but I recommend taking all his classes
Great lecturer, explained everything clearly and willing to answer questions.

He's a very easy marker but not the greatest teacher. He makes it easy to get bonus marks and is very lenient, but he doesn't explain the material very well. If you have friends in the class and can learn together, it will be a breeze. No textbook use at all which was a blessing.
By far my favourite prof at U of O. He is fair, friendly, and has a very clear way of explaining concepts. He truly wants his students to succeed and prepares us very well for the exam. Five star.

Beware of his midterm on excel, long case study with 20 questions to complete in 2 hours. He tailors the class heavily on the service sector of operations, so your class is different than the typical operation management class. The final was 4 case studies but they were shorter/easier than the one on the midterm. Recommend taking another professor.
Makes lots of mistakes when lecturing

his lectures are all over the place, very unorganized, and sometimes he contradicts himself and makes mistakes. His lectures were a waste of time, which is unfortunate because lectures are important for subjects like statistics. The book was all I used.

Gives you all the details for the Midterm and Final in the class to ensure that as a student you are well aware of what you will be tested on. He is a very intellectual prof who wants his students to succeed. If you listen to all his tips and do all the practices tests you will be fine for the final. Assignments and finals  are straight forward

His classes are not always the most loved classes from the telfer students. The only thing i want to say is that if you are on here choosing whose class to register in for Stats, BDM or Ops, choose him! He cares more about his students and delivers the content the best.
All over the place nice guy tho
Great prof! Lectures can become long but he makes an effort to keep you interested, always available if you have questions after class. His feedback is very helpful
Best prof. Take him if you have the choice

I had this prof for BDM and Stats 1 and he was great in both. He gives good feedback and has really good lecture slides. BDM can be challenging but he tried to make sure that all the students understood the content. I finished with an A+ in both the classes I took with him and would definitely take this prof again if I had the chance.
Telfer lost a great professor !
Great professor in class. Makes a boring class kind of interesting. Very clear in his teaching as well as what will be on the exams. Assignments were slightly difficult but not impossible.
Be prepared for his final exam as it is going to be tough. Midterm is quite easy ;you could get a A, but the final could fail you.
Best stats prof. Hilarious and easy to understand. Got an A+ on the first midterm and 100% on all assignments. Would definitely recommend to anyone

Had him for BDM, Stats 1, & Ops. They are not the easiest classes for the average student so you need to work to properly understand (in all of them, if you don't understand it, the cheat sheet is no help and you'll fail). Exams are tough, but Davood prepares you the best in comparison to other profs/sections. He's young and gets to the point.

Awesome prof, he's a great teacher and will do his best to make you pass. HOWEVER, his exams are extremely difficult. The questions he gives in the exam and midterm are WAY harder than the examples given in class, pre-final review session, assigned questions, and assignments.   If you want to LEARN, take him. If you want a GOOD GRADE, don't.

Great Prof! Really care about the success of his students Made very goodclear Powerpoint slides and posted them on Blackboard. There are assignments due every 2 to 3 weeks but they are pretty easy if you read the textbook. You are allowed a cheat sheet at the midterm and final exam, if you take the info he provided on his slides, you'll pass!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'EXTRA CREDIT']

rComments: Only prof at the University of Ottawa I have had for two separate courses. Like him in BDM, and he was even better for stats. Funny and relaxed demeanor in class makes for a more enjoyable class environment.  Writes his own exams to make sure they are fair. Best prof I've had so far.
Really nice and willing to help
Fortunately this course runs several sections in parallel, so i say telfer remains an Okay place to learn business statistics, but, ...
Great prof and literally does everything in his power to help the students. If you have the chance take him!!

He's a great prof. Has AMAZING notes. Gives good examples in lectures and knows his stuff too. If you're struggling with a specific concepts he's wiling to help. He's also pretty funny and likes to keep things interesting. This is the go-to prof for ADM2303. Our class had the highest average for the Stats 1 section.
He is a very young professor, very good, and explain stuff very clear. He will tell students what the test would be, recommend.
He will tell you everything you need to know, great teacher
Horrible experience overall.
awesome :)

A very young professor. Is actually very good for teaching stats. I had Suren Phansalker before and had to drop his stats class. he was awful. This guy is easy to understand. Class itself can be boring but the powerpoints make up for it. Assignments are fairly easy. 80% of it we handed in instead of using mystatlab. 75% + on all assignments so far.
Probably one of the best teachers that can teach Business Decision Models very well.
Good , but not great!
He might not be a really awesome teacher, its just his first year so he is still nervous. Go to his review sessions are very helpful and he is a very nice guy. is also lenient with marks
Mr. Davood is not a good prof. He shouldn't teaching Operations Management nor Business Decision Models. This a very new area for him. Should see something different in his field.
What's wrong with this prof. doesn't teach well and makes the class confused. He has no talents whatsoever.
I like his style of teaching. Lecture notes are great.
Not a good Prof. for teaching. Needs to be organised, prepared for class, answer questions not just turning around with the answers. Be direct and stop wasting our time and knowledge.
Very confusing class and prof. unable to explain.

I had OPS with his in fall. I loved his style of teaching throughout the semester.He was able to speak about reality rather than constant theory being thrown in our faces. He is really modest and for the first time in  Telfer courses I didn't feel like the Professor was talking down to the students.
I'm totally unhappy with his teaching. Confusing and not clear.
Confusing class and not clear at all.
I'm currently taking ADM3301M with prof. Davood but honestly, he knows absolutely nothing on OM. He needs more help than some students.
Great class.
Great guy! I think the 3 consecutive terrible ratings were made by the same person and don't give him justice. I'd definitely recommend taking a class with him.

Excellent professor! Course content is useful & fun to learn. If done right, the 25% project is a blast! Exams were fair. My advice - study slides and only use the textbook as a reference when clarity on a specific topic is needed.
He's not a good prof. Needs to be vry well prepared before coming to class and answer the questions. Don't ply around.
I didn't learn anything from this course. Prof Davood is not up to the level. Needs to be replaced.
He's not a good prof. Himself needs help to understand the cocepts of operations management
Great professor. Excellent explaination. Make the class very interesting and enjoyable.
I like him. He's a really nice guy and wants people to actually learn something rather than just regurgitate concepts.
He's really clear and his assignments reflect material taught. His exams are very similar to assignments. Take as many classes with him as you can. Easy A+, just do what he recommends.
Davood is Awesome! Very knowledgeable and smart guy, Well organized,clear and helpful. On top of that he is a super nice person.Highly recommend.

Davood Astaraky is an excellent professor. He genuinely cares about his students, is enthusiastic about the subject matter and always available for questions. Overall, he made what I found in the past to be a very difficult subject (having registered and dropped this class before) easy and enjoyable to learn!

I love Davood, he's a young prof with a very good heart and as the semester goes on, I like him more and more! His assignments are longer than the ones given by other profs but they prepare you super well for midterms. And midterms are really easy!!! As a student, that's all I ask for... haha take him for sure!

He is new and young best best prof you could ask for. Very helpful, very fair, gives thorough explanations without ever being condescending, and knows how to teach so that students understand. His slides are amazing and he uses exciting materials to teach. Also an all-around nice guy, and pretty funny as well.

This prof is new and I have him in both BDM and stats. He is great! He's a quiet guy and sometime doesn't speak loud enough but his explanations and slides are amazing! I really like him and recommend him, he simplifies the subject matter. Intelligent and modest man - thank you!
